Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with locating the source of diffusion in complex networks, which is a common problem in social and information networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses efficient implementations of the proposed strategy. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper mentions the Internet as an example of a real network. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper describes the complexity of the proposed strategy. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with estimating the location of the source from measurements collected by sparsely-placed observers, which involves information theory concepts.
